s can be optimal, in different circumstances? This book shows how these and many other questions can be answered. The mathematics involved is explained very simply, with biology students in mind, but the book is not just for them. It is also for professionals, ranging from teachers to researchers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Evolution.2bisacsh  aAssessor strategy.  aBarbary doves.  aBourgeois strategy.  aCuckolder strategy.  aDove strategy.  aHaplochromis.  aHawk strategy.  aJunco.  aMaxwell convention.  aOnchorhynchus.  aPararge aegeria.  aPterophylium.  aVespinae.  aViverridae.  aZyxomma.  aalbatrosses.  aangelfish.  abang-bang control.  abuckling.  abutterflies.  acatastrophe theory.  aclutch size.  acomputer simulation.  adynamic programming.  aefficiency.  aenergy intake.  afeeding strategies.  afitness component.  agames theory.  agradient.  agrowth and reproduction.  aintegrals.  aintercept.  amarginal value theorem.  aqueens.  ared deer.  arisk of starvation.  arotifer.  asection modulus.  asemicircular canals.  astate variable.  aterritories.  atortoises.  awalking.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691221601zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691221601423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691221601.jpg  a978-3-11-044249-6  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999c1927d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK